turn.2: Sulitjelma (mountain) Sulitjelma (, Pite Sami: "Sulidälbmá/Sulidælbmá") is a mountain massif on the Norway-Sweden border in the municipality of Fauske in Nordland, Norway and the municipality of Arjeplog in Norrbotten, Sweden.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: The massif lies east of the village of Sulitjelma, which takes its name from the mountain.
turn.5: What else is known about the mountain?
turn.6: The massif is bordered by "Låmivatnet" (Lake Låmi) and "Muorkkejávrre" (Lake Muorkke) to the south, and by "Bajep Sårjåsjávrre" (Upper Lake Sårjås) and "Vuolep Sårjåsjávrre" (Lower Lake Sårjås) to the north.
turn.7: What is the importance of the mountain?
turn.8: About two-thirds of the mountain is in Norway.
turn.9: Is there anything else that is known about the mountain?
turn.10: The Langvann Valley extends toward the massif along a northwest-southeast axis, through which the Sjønstå River (, known as the "Langvasselva" in its upper course) flows, forming the Sulitjelma watercourse.
turn.12: The valley starts at the village of Sjønstå on "Øvervatnet" (Upper Lake), which lies about east of the village of Sulitjelma itself.
